The Nigeria Immigration Service (NIS) has announced the death of a Deputy Comptroller General of Immigration, DCG Raymond Tonye Akra Jaja in charge of the Directorate of Border management at the headquarters in Abuja. A statement by NIS spokesman, Sunday James, yesterday said DCG Jaja died on June 9, after a brief illness. James said Jaja died at 58 years old. “The Comptroller General of the Nigeria Immigration Service Muhammad Babandede said late DCG Jaja would be remembered for his high sense of discipline and uncommon loyalty to constituted authorities.”